Sephardic Haroset (Dried Fruit and Nut Chutney)

1 tsp whole black peppercorns, toasted
6 whole cloves, toasted
4 green cardamom pods, toasted
1/2 c toasted almonds, finely chopped
1/2 c raw shelled pistachios, finely chopped
1/2 c pommegranate juice
2 tbsp pomegranate molasses
2 tbsp cinnamon
2 tbsp white sesame seeds. toasted
2 tsp salt
20 (5 oz) dried apricots, finely chopped
10 (2.5 oz) dried black figs, finely chopped
10 (3oz) pitted prunes, finely chopped
10 (3oz) pitted medjool dates, finely chopped

Using a mortar and pestle, grind the toasted peppercorns, cloves, and cardamom pods into a fine powder. Transfer to a medium bowl and fold in the rest of the ingredients until a paste comes together. Serve alongside matzo.
